  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "3vyxkgZUjRXlB8orlQZPhaojvPM=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:28.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "## GQL + Swarm Dual Sync\n\nIn one browser, PGlite acts as the hub between two worlds:\n\n- **Switchboard world**: remote drives pulled in via GQL channels.\n- **Swarm world**: drives and documents mirrored out to encrypted feeds.\n\nEach drive is independent:\n\n- Drive A: pulled from Switchboard (GQL) **and** pushed to Swarm Feed A.\n- Drive B: same dual path.\n- Drive C: locally created by the user, only pushed to Swarm Feed C (no Switchboard counterpart).\n\n### Why it works\n\nBoth channels read from the same `operation_index_operations` table, where every op gets a global ordinal. Each remote has an independent cursor in `sync_cursors`, so progress on one channel never interferes with the other.\n\n`SyncManager` orchestrates both transparently \u2014 it does not know whether a given remote is GQL or Swarm, it just pumps operations through `channel.outbox` / `channel.inbox` / `channel.deadLetter`.\n\nThis is the foundation that lets Connect work decentralized-first while retaining compatibility with Switchboard-hosted drives.",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:28.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:28.000Z"
    }
  },
